Property.name: InsuranceMatchMode
Property.Description:
A setting on the interface controls whether matching is performed using the contents of IN1.49 or the following three fields:
  • Insurance Co (using ID (IN1.3) or (Name (IN1.4) and Address (IN1.5)) if IN1.3 is blank)
  • Policy # (IN1.36)
  • Group # (IN1.8)

Property.name: SnapshotMode
Property.Description:
Snapshot All Option -

This option will cause the interface to first error out ALL insurance records linked to a patient regardless of who they were added by in the system. Each loop of the IN1 repetitions will then re-enable each insurance company record on the patient based on the chosen match criteria defined in 2.1. Non-matching insurance records will be added to the patient. The first IN1 in the message should be marked primary and dates of validity from the IN1 segments should also be supported and update the appropriate table flags.
Snapshot Own Option -

This option will cause the interface to first error out only insurance records last modified by that interface. This would be used in situations where the practice enters some of their own insurance records in to the system or there are multiple HIS systems feeding ARIA and the customer does not want them to overwrite each other's insurance. Each loop of the IN1 repetitions will then re-enable each insurance company record on the patient based on the chosen match criteria in 2.1. Non-matching insurance records will be added to the patient. The first IN1 should be marked primary and dates of validity from the IN1 segment should also be supported and update the appropriate table flags.

Method.name: OnPage
Method.Implementation:
// Step 3 - run tests and display the results &html< Varian Unit Testing Portal 
	>

	// Step 1 - configure environment for unit testing
	if ( '$Data(^UnitTestRoot) ) {
		set ^UnitTestRoot="C:\InterSystems\UnitTests\"
		$$$THROWONERROR(sc,##Class(%File).CreateDirectoryChain(^UnitTestRoot))
		write "Created ^UnitTestRoot @ "_^UnitTestRoot,!
		$$$THROWONERROR(sc,##Class(%File).CreateDirectoryChain(^UnitTestRoot_"VarianTests"))
		write "Created ^UnitTestRoot @ "_^UnitTestRoot_"VarianTests",!

	} else {
		write "^UnitTestRoot="_^UnitTestRoot_" exists!",!
	}
	// Step 2 - export the unit tests
	// find all subsclasses on %UnitTest in varian.tests
	set rs=##class(%ResultSet).%New()
	set sc=rs.Prepare("select Name from %Dictionary.CompiledClass where Name %STARTSWITH 'varian.tests' and Super = '%UnitTest.TestCase'")
	set sc=rs.Execute()
	while ( rs.Next() ) {
		set name=rs.Get("Name")
		set exportFile=^UnitTestRoot_"VarianTests\"_name_".cls.xml"
		write "exportFile=",exportFile,!
		do $system.OBJ.Export(name_".cls",exportFile)
			
	}
	
	zw ^UnitTestRoot
	Do ##class(%UnitTest.Manager).RunTest("VarianTests","/nodelete")
	
	Set s = ##class(%RoutineMgr).GetWebServerPort(.p, .h, .up, .url)
	if $E(url,$L(url))="/" {
		set url=$E(url,1,$L(url)-1)
	}
	If ($$$ISERR(s)) || ($G(url)="") Set url = "http://127.0.0.1:57772"
	set url=url_$$getDefaultApp^%SYS.cspServer2($ZU(5))
	set resultsLink=url_"/%25UnitTest.Portal.Indices.cls?Index="_(^UnitTest.Result-1)
	
	&html<
#(resultsLink)# > Quit $$$OK

Method.name: VarianDocumentBinaryContentToBase64List
Method.Implementation:
set list=##class(%ListOfDataTypes).%New() set b64Stream=##class(%Stream.TmpCharacter).%New() do b64Stream.Write($system.Encryption.Base64Encode(doc.BinaryContent)) set chunkSize=76 set chunkCount=0 do b64Stream.Rewind() while ( 'b64Stream.AtEnd ) { set chunk=b64Stream.Read(chunkSize+2) set line=$extract(chunk,1,(chunkSize-2)) do list.Insert(line)
}

Method.name: VarianDocumentBinaryContentToList

set list=##class(%ListOfDataTypes).%New() set b64Stream=##class(%Stream.TmpCharacter).%New() do b64Stream.Write($system.Encryption.Base64Encode(doc.BinaryContent)) set chunkSize=76 set chunkCount=0 do b64Stream.Rewind() while ( 'b64Stream.AtEnd ) { set chunk=b64Stream.Read(chunkSize+2) set line=$extract(chunk,1,(chunkSize-2)) do list.Insert(line)
} return list
